    "There is a genuine danger that advanced AI capabilities could become concentrated in the hands of a privileged few nations, corporations, or elite groups.",
    "True democratization in education demands that we foster ecosystems where AI development is a participatory endeavor, drawing from the experience of teachers, students, and assessment professionals within government and industry.",
    "We can only shape AI to be genuinely universally beneficial through multi-stakeholder collaboration.",
    "Seeking the best way to foster such ecosystems requires careful consideration and ensuring that our AI systems align with and abide by human values.Gorgun & Bulut, 2021; Lindner et al., 2019; Liu et al., 2020; Yildirim-Erbasli & Bulut, 2022).",
    "Typically, the data would not include the ground truth about aberrant responses, so the problem is approached from an outlier or anomaly detection perspective."
